59
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:54,660
Shelley, my room is fantastic!

60
00:02:54,660 --> 00:02:55,780
So glad you like it!

61
00:02:55,780 --> 00:02:56,680
You were right.

62
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:57,730
This cultural tour

63
00:02:57,730 --> 00:02:59,019
was an amazing idea.

64
00:02:59,019 --> 00:03:01,310
Well I’m glad to hear you say that

65
00:03:01,310 --> 00:03:04,890
because I’ve signed you up for a very special

66
00:03:04,890 --> 00:03:07,209
traditional Taiwanese shoemaking class.

67
00:03:07,209 --> 00:03:09,430
Oh, that’s fantastic!

68
00:03:09,430 --> 00:03:11,459
You know, a man really should be able

69
00:03:11,459 --> 00:03:12,580
to make his own shoes.

70
00:03:12,580 --> 00:03:13,980
You’re so right.

71
00:03:13,980 --> 00:03:14,880
Let’s go.

72
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:18,960
Well, here we are.

73
00:03:18,970 --> 00:03:21,849
Traditional women’s cloth shoes.

74
00:03:21,849 --> 00:03:25,080
Oh, you didn’t say it was women’s shoes.

75
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,260
Oh didn’t I?

76
00:03:26,260 --> 00:03:28,500
That’s great, I’ll give it a shot!

77
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:29,500
Really?

78
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:31,440
Yeah, thanks Shelley!

79
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,840
Hotel staff were kind enough to show me the
ropes

80
00:03:57,920 --> 00:04:00,960
